Package com.github.seqware.queryengine.factory

Provides the classes that the RESTful interface will use to construct interfaces that use the back-end without reference to the specific back-end.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
CreateUpdateManager A very simple Manager that is somewhat like a very stripped down EntityManager from JPA allowing us to create Models and persist them, in other words this handles Create and Update operations out of the basic CRUD operations.
 

Class Summary
SWQEFactory This is the SeqWare Query Engine factory and should be used as the primary entry-point for developers.
 

Enum Summary
CreateUpdateManager.State This manager defines Atoms to be in the following states
SWQEFactory.Model_Type ' These types describe different types of our model objects, for example the in memory objects load everything into memory.
SWQEFactory.Serialization_Type These describe different types of serialization only
SWQEFactory.Storage_Type These describe different types of our back-end, whether we store to files, to a database, or simply keep things in memory
 

Package com.github.seqware.queryengine.factory Description

Provides the classes that the RESTful interface will use to construct interfaces that use the back-end without reference to the specific back-end.
